sourcesContent: import { SinglePost, SinglePostImage, SinglePostTitle, SinglePostInfo, Span, Name, SinglePostDescription, Introduction, } from './Singlepost.styled' import Music from '../../image/Kpop.jpeg' import EditDelete from '../icons /EditDelete' const SinglePostMusic = () => { return ( My Favourite music Author: Dohee Lee 4 hours ago Kpop! These music has been my favourie since i was young. I remember listening to my first kpop music when i was 7 years old. It was "Into The New World" by Girls Generation, which i found extremely fascinating as i have never seen artists where they sing and dance at the same time! The music is very unique even if its similar to Western or pop music and unlike the other pop artists, kpop performance is beyond the top as they have amazing choreographies. Pop music is a genre, K-pop doesn’t stick to one genre, edm or ballads could still be considered as K-pop but not necessarily pop. K-pop, I think, isn’t a genre of music. It’s just music made by Korean artists or musicians from Korea so I don’t think there’s any practical way to compare it to a music genre. ) } export default SinglePostMusic
